HEADWORD: Tschego
<hw>Tsche"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From a native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A West African anthropoid ape
allied to the gorilla and chimpanzee, and by some considered only a
variety of the chimpanzee. It is noted for building large,
umbrella-shaped nests in trees. Called also <altname>tscheigo</altname>,
<altname>tschiego</altname>, <altname>nschego</altname>,
<altname>nscheigo</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tsebe</ent>⟦br⟧
